2. ERD(DBML 기반)

아래는 논리 데이터 모델을 DBML(Database Markup Language) 형식으로 표현한 ERD이다.

```dbml
Table PARTICIPANT {
  participant_id bigint [pk]
  participant_code varchar [unique, not null]
  participant_status_code varchar
  gender_code varchar
  birth_year int
  registered_at datetime
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
  created_by varchar
  updated_by varchar
}

Table PARTICIPANT_ACCOUNT {
  participant_account_id bigint [pk]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  login_code varchar [unique, not null]
  login_status_code varchar
  login_fail_count int
  last_login_at datetime
  session_token_hash varchar
  token_expires_at datetime
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table DEVICE {
  device_id bigint [pk]
  device_serial_no varchar [unique, not null]
  device_type_code varchar
  device_model varchar
  firmware_version varchar
  app_version varchar
  android_version varchar
  phone_model varchar
  device_status_code varchar
  registered_at datetime
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
  created_by varchar
  updated_by varchar
}

Table PARTICIPANT_DEVICE {
  participant_device_id bigint [pk]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  device_id bigint [ref: > DEVICE.device_id]
  assigned_at datetime
  unassigned_at datetime
  mapping_status_code varchar
  remark text
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
  created_by varchar
  updated_by varchar
}

Table SYNC_SESSION {
  sync_session_id bigint [pk]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  participant_device_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT_DEVICE.participant_device_id]
  started_at datetime
  finished_at datetime
  sync_status_code varchar
  source_code varchar
  total_records int
  success_records int
  failed_records int
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
  created_by varchar
  updated_by varchar
}

Table COLLECTION_LOG {
  collection_log_id bigint [pk]
  sync_session_id bigint [ref: > SYNC_SESSION.sync_session_id]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  participant_device_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT_DEVICE.participant_device_id]
  endpoint varchar
  api_version varchar
  request_id varchar [unique]
  transaction_id varchar
  received_at datetime
  processed_at datetime
  collection_status_code varchar
  http_status int
  error_message text
  retry_count int
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table ADMIN_USER {
  admin_user_id bigint [pk]
  login_id varchar [unique, not null]
  password_hash varchar
  role_code varchar
  is_active boolean
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
  last_login_at datetime
}

Table MEASUREMENT_TYPE {
  measurement_type_id bigint [pk]
  metric_code varchar [unique, not null]
  metric_name varchar
  unit varchar
  category_code varchar
  is_active boolean
  display_order int
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table LIFESTYLE_DATA {
  lifestyle_data_id bigint [pk]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  measurement_type_id bigint [ref: > MEASUREMENT_TYPE.measurement_type_id]
  collection_log_id bigint [ref: > COLLECTION_LOG.collection_log_id]
  measured_at datetime
  value_type_code varchar
  numeric_value decimal
  value_text varchar
  metadata_json json
  source_code varchar
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table DOWNLOAD_HISTORY {
  download_id bigint [pk]
  admin_user_id bigint [ref: > ADMIN_USER.admin_user_id]
  start_date date
  end_date date
  filter_condition varchar
  file_name varchar
  downloaded_at datetime
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table DOWNLOAD_PARTICIPANT {
  download_participant_id bigint [pk]
  download_id bigint [ref: > DOWNLOAD_HISTORY.download_id]
  participant_id bigint [ref: > PARTICIPANT.participant_id]
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table CODE_MASTER {
  code_master_id bigint [pk]
  domain_code varchar [unique, not null]
  domain_name varchar
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}

Table CODE_DETAIL {
  code_detail_id bigint [pk]
  code_master_id bigint [ref: > CODE_MASTER.code_master_id]
  code_value varchar [not null]
  code_name varchar
  description varchar
  is_active boolean
  sort_order int
  created_at datetime
  updated_at datetime
}
```

## 2.1 ERD 설계 포인트
- 참여자를 중심으로 장치, 동기화 세션, 수집 로그 및 라이프로그 데이터를 계층적으로 연결하여 데이터 생성부터 저장까지의 데이터 흐름을 추적할 수 있도록 설계하였다.
- 시계열 라이프로그 데이터와 수집 이력을 분리하여 데이터 생성부터 저장까지의 Audit Trail을 지원하도록 설계하였다.
- 상태값 및 분류값은 공통 코드(CODE_MASTER, CODE_DETAIL) 체계를 통해 표준화하였다.
- 다운로드 이력과 다운로드 대상자를 교차 엔티티(DOWNLOAD_PARTICIPANT)로 분리하여 다대다(N:M) 관계를 정규화하였다.
- 측정 항목(MEASUREMENT_TYPE)을 별도 관리하여 신규 생체지표 추가 시 스키마 변경 없이 확장 가능하도록 설계하였다.

## 2.2 주요 관계
- PARTICIPANT(1) : (N) PARTICIPANT_ACCOUNT
- PARTICIPANT(1) : (N) PARTICIPANT_DEVICE
- DEVICE(1) : (N) PARTICIPANT_DEVICE
- PARTICIPANT_DEVICE(1) : (N) SYNC_SESSION
- SYNC_SESSION(1) : (N) COLLECTION_LOG
- PARTICIPANT(1) : (N) LIFESTYLE_DATA
- COLLECTION_LOG(1) : (N) LIFESTYLE_DATA
- MEASUREMENT_TYPE(1) : (N) LIFESTYLE_DATA
- ADMIN_USER(1) : (N) DOWNLOAD_HISTORY
- DOWNLOAD_HISTORY(1) : (N) DOWNLOAD_PARTICIPANT
- PARTICIPANT(1) : (N) DOWNLOAD_PARTICIPANT
- CODE_MASTER(1) : (N) CODE_DETAIL
